You are given a 2D integer array squares. Each squares[i] = [xi, yi, li] represents the coordinates of the bottom-left point and the side length of a square parallel to the x-axis.

Find the minimum y-coordinate value of a horizontal line such that the total area of the squares above the line equals the total area of the squares below the line.

Answers within 10-5 of the actual answer will be accepted.

Note: Squares may overlap. Overlapping areas should be counted multiple times.

 

Example 1:

Input: squares = [[0,0,1],[2,2,1]]

Output: 1.00000

Explanation:



Any horizontal line between y = 1 and y = 2 will have 1 square unit above it and 1 square unit below it. The lowest option is 1.

Example 2:

Input: squares = [[0,0,2],[1,1,1]]

Output: 1.16667

Explanation:



The areas are:

Below the line: 7/6 * 2 (Red) + 1/6 (Blue) = 15/6 = 2.5.
Above the line: 5/6 * 2 (Red) + 5/6 (Blue) = 15/6 = 2.5.
Since the areas above and below the line are equal, the output is 7/6 = 1.16667.

 

Constraints:

1 <= squares.length <= 5 * 10^4
squares[i] = [xi, yi, li]
squares[i].length == 3
0 <= xi, yi <= 10^9
1 <= li <= 10^9
The total area of all the squares will not exceed 10^12.

Code: //O(n * log R )

class Solution {
    public double separateSquares(int[][] squares) {
        double totalArea = 0;
        double low = Double.MAX_VALUE, high = 0;

        for (int[] s : squares) {
            double y = s[1], l = s[2];
            totalArea += l * l;
            low = Math.min(low, y);
            high = Math.max(high, y + l);
        }

        double target = totalArea / 2.0;

        while (high - low > 1e-5) { // enough for 1e-6 precision
            double mid = (low + high) / 2;
            double below = 0;

            for (int[] s : squares) {
                double y = s[1], l = s[2];

                if (mid <= y) {
                    // contributes nothing
                } else if (mid >= y + l) {
                    below += l * l;
                } else {
                    below += l * (mid - y);
                }
            }

            if (below < target) {
                low = mid;
            } else {
                high = mid;
            }
        }

        return low;
    }
}

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Debug statements: EXTRA

Just to see debug statements for example 1 and example 2 : You will get Output Limit Exceeded error if you submit solution with debug statements :)

class Solution {
    public double separateSquares(int[][] squares) {
        double totalArea = 0;
        double low = Double.MAX_VALUE, high = 0;

        DecimalFormat df = new DecimalFormat("0.0000000000");

        // Initial scan
        for (int[] s : squares) {
            double y = s[1], l = s[2];
            totalArea += l * l;
            low = Math.min(low, y);
            high = Math.max(high, y + l);
        }

        double target = totalArea / 2.0;

        System.out.println("Total Area = " + totalArea);
        System.out.println("Target Area (Below) = " + target);
        System.out.println("Initial Search Range: low = " + low + ", high = " + high);
        System.out.println("--------------------------------------------------");

        int iter = 0;

        while (high - low > 1e-5) {

            double mid = (low + high) / 2;
            double below = 0;

            System.out.println("Iteration " + iter++);
            System.out.println("mid = " + mid);

            for (int i = 0; i < squares.length; i++) {
                double y = squares[i][1];
                double l = squares[i][2];
                double contribution;

                if (mid <= y) {
                    contribution = 0;
                } else if (mid >= y + l) {
                    contribution = l * l;
                } else {
                    contribution = l * (mid - y);
                }

                below += contribution;

                System.out.println(
                    "  Square " + i +
                    " [y=" + y + ", l=" + l + "] contributes below area = " + contribution
                );
            }
          
            System.out.println("Total below area = " + below);

            if (below < target) {
                System.out.println("below < target → moving low up");
                low = mid;
            } else {
                System.out.println("below >= target → moving high down");
                high = mid;
            }

            System.out.println("Updated range: low = " + low + ", high = " + high);
            System.out.println("--------------------------------------------------");

            System.out.println(" high minus low difference (check if less than 0.00001)= " + df.format(high - low ));
        }

        System.out.println("Final Answer ≈ " + low);
        System.out.println(
            "Loop exited because (high - low) = " + df.format(high - low)
            + " <= 0.00001"
        );
        return low;
    }
}



